Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1,535,951.24 and Total Revenue = 7,825,951.24  
• Calculation: (1,535,951.24 / 7,825,951.24) × 100 ≈ 19.63%

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –4,398,760.38  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 2,491,297.55  
• Calculation: –4,398,760.38 / 2,491,297.55 ≈ –1.76

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "19.63%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-1.76"
  }
}
